<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-66-1076 </DOCNO><TEXT>This paper provides a general overview of technical methods for assessingthe operational risks associated with energy production at wind parks.The scope of the paper is limited to production oriented rather thansafety or liability associated risks. The methods presented are the uncertaintymethod, fault-tree methods, probabilistic methods, and the reliability-centeredmethod. The various strengths and weaknesses of each method are discussed.</TEXT></DOC>